    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1866-07-30T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1866-07-30T00:00:00-05:00" n="400" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d400">
                <head>
                    <persName type="from">Mr. Seward</persName> to <persName type="to">Mr.
                                Williams</persName>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 33.]</seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>, </placeName>
                        <date calendar="gregorian" when="1866-07-30">
                            <hi rend="italic">July</hi> 30, 1866.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: Your despatch of the 12th of April last,
                            No. 30, in regard to the desecration of the American cemetery at
                            Tangchau, has been received.</p>
                <p>I will thank you to inform me what is the custom of guarding foreign
                            cemeteries in China; whether the government charges itself with the
                            duty, or is it assumed by foreign residents, or their consuls. You may
                            make inquiries, and send me a careful report upon the whole subject.</p>
                <p>I am, sir, your obedient servant,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>WILLIAM H. SEWARD.</signed>
                </closer>
                <postscript>
                    <p>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">S. Wells Williams</hi>, Esq.,<hi rend="italic">
                                    &amp;c., &amp;c., &amp;c</hi>.</p>
                </postscript>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
